  <prompt>
    Implement SignalEvaluationService: evaluate SpendSnapshots against threshold rules.
    BudgetExceeded at 100%+ spend, BudgetWarning at configurable % (default 80%),
    VelocitySpike at configurable % increase (default 50%). Upsert SpendSignal records.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Expert in rule-based evaluation and Dataverse entity operations.
    Follow deterministic computation patterns — no AI involved in signal evaluation.
  </role>

  <goal>
    SignalEvaluationService created with EvaluateAsync method. Evaluates SpendSnapshots against
    configurable threshold rules. Creates SpendSignal records for budget exceeded, budget warning,
    and velocity spike conditions.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The SignalEvaluationService runs after snapshot generation to detect financial anomalies.
      It evaluates the latest spend snapshots against configurable threshold rules:

      - BudgetExceeded: fires when spend >= 100% of budget (always active, not configurable)
      - BudgetWarning: fires when spend >= configurable% of budget (default 80%)
      - VelocitySpike: fires when MoM velocity increase >= configurable% (default 50%)

      Signals are upserted to SpendSignal records in Dataverse. These power the "Active Signals"
      section of the Finance PCF panel.

      This is purely deterministic rule evaluation — no AI involved.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Finance/SpendSnapshotService.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
